## SCORING: WORKFLOW EFFICIENCY (this specialist owns)

Weighted composite of 7 subscores, each 0-100:

```
Workflow Efficiency = A×0.20 + B×0.15 + C×0.15 + D×0.15 + E×0.15 + F×0.10 + G×0.10
```

| Score | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| 90-100 | Triggers consistently absent. Workflows are streamlined and resilient. |
| 70-89 | Occasional inefficiencies. Functional but has friction. |
| <70 | Multiple triggers. Users regularly hit workflow friction or data loss. |

Count signals only for patterns present in scoped files.

### Signal Checklist

**+1 each**: form auto-saves, equipment/values pre-filled, critical flow completable without leaving page, progress indicator on multi-step, filters persist, bulk operation available, smart defaults used, success confirmation (toast/redirect/celebration), offline queue on field form, draft recovery on return, template/duplicate available for daily forms, compliance completion tracking visible, wizard step synced to URL.

**-1 each**: form data lost on navigation, no pre-fill for repeated values, critical flow >5 unnecessary steps, no progress save on wizard, filter resets, no confirmation on success, key action >4 clicks deep, no offline support on field form (if app has offline capability), no draft recovery, daily form has no "quick fill" path, compliance status not visible on dashboard.

```
Report:
Workflow Efficiency: [score]
  A) Task Flow: [subscore] — [justification]
  B) Navigation: [subscore] — [justification]
  C) Data Entry: [subscore] — [justification]
