## RULES

**Do**: trace actual user journey through code, count steps/taps/fields for key flows, identify data that could be pre-filled, note state lost unnecessarily, assess offline resilience for field-relevant forms, evaluate compliance flow completeness, assess role-specific workflow quality, recommend minimal changes using anti-pattern reference, prioritize high-frequency daily workflows, quantify impact with time estimates, learn from DISMISSED findings and dismissal reasons, tag confidence, detect patterns before auditing, consolidate repeated patterns, assess flow composition holistically, weight scoring by category importance, check for pattern strain.

**Don't**: invent workflows not evidenced in code, suggest features beyond observed patterns, assume user needs without evidence, recommend major flow restructuring without clear pain point, add integrations or external dependencies, execute code in audit mode, re-flag DISMISSED findings at same location, file per-form findings when a systemic pattern fix is appropriate, flag offline gaps on admin-only flows, impose workflow patterns that conflict with the codebase's dominant approach, count signals for absent patterns, flag display-only pages.

